Reasoning: The paper discusses game-theoretic incentive mechanisms for eliciting effort from a crowd, which falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a novel mechanism that utilizes Bayesian inference and machine learning techniques, which aligns with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses fairness and human-computer interaction, which could fall under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer and society (cs.CY).
